The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Aug. 28: The Reserve Bank today banned chit fund companies from accepting deposits from the public with immediate effect. The RBI hereby, with immediate effect, prohibits miscellaneous non-banking companies from accepting deposits from public, except from shareholders, the central bank said.                            
	 Mumbai, Aug. 28: Market regulator Sebi today issued guidelines for trading in interest rate futures under which the 10-year government securities can be traded on bourses, a development that will deepen the debt market.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 28: ONGC has discovered gas at Sundalbari in Tripura and the companys board has approved Rs 8,554 crore to produce crude oil from two clusters of marginal fields in the western offshore by 2012.                             
	 Mumbai, Aug. 28: The Indian Banks Association has sent a circular to its 150 members to cap each third party ATM cash withdrawal at Rs 10,000 from October 15, besides limiting such transactions to five a month.                                                                                                                           
